<br>
Yes the fact that it casts a manaless RUNE IV while still using the peridot makes it just about useless.  Why waste a 10pp peridot on RUVE IV when you can get the added hp buff of RUNE V for the same cost?<br>
<br>
The only time I have ever used the robe effect is when I was helping buff lvl 40ish characters for Vox or Naggy raids.  Some of them don't have the level requirement for RUNE V, so I use the robe on them.  And that's about it.. I've never used it for anything else, but I don't mind... the stats are still nice.<br>
<br>
You could also consider the &quot;usefullness&quot; of the effect on the Thurg bracer.  Reclaim Energy?!  I can't remember the last time I even cast a pet.  So needless to say I have never once cast the effect on the bracer (actually I think the stats on the Thurg bracer are pretty crappy, so even though I had the armor and three gems, I still just MQed it to another caster in my guild).<br>
<br>
The pants and the slippers do have fairly usefull effects on them though.  Being able to cast C1 on beggers who are too low in level for C2 (pre level 59 and GoPT) is nice.  Also casting invis on other members in my group using my slippers is something I do almost on a daily basis.<br>
